parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure (Gasoline Odor in Cabin)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause a strong gasoline odor to enter the passenger cabin, posing a fire hazard and health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor in the passenger cabin
especially in cold weather
when starting the car
or when using the heater fan.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel lines or hoses can cause a fuel leak, leading to a fire hazard and health risk to occupants.
symptoms: Fuel smell in the passenger cabin
fuel leak visible under the hood
hesitation or surging when driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine hesitation or surging can cause a loss of power, leading to a potential accident or near-miss situation.
symptoms: Engine hesitation or surging
especially when accelerating or merging into traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling or hesitation can cause loss of power, difficulty shifting gears, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling or hesitation when accelerating
especially from a stop; difficulty shifting gears; loss of power; sudden stalling without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, coolant leaks, and engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: Engine overheating; coolant leaks; loss of engine power; engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gas leaks and fuel system issues can cause fires, explosions, and safety hazards.
symptoms: Strong gas smell in the engine compartment and passenger compartment; gas leaks; engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure and timing belt issues can cause loss of power, engine damage, and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: Engine failure; loss of power; timing belt breakage; engine stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch issues can cause difficulty shifting gears, loss of power, and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; clutch pedal sticks to the floor; difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, and damage to property, as the vehicle may suddenly lunge forward or accelerate without the driver's input.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
the throttle sticks
the vehicle takes off on its own
the vehicle hesitates and then lunges forward
the brake pedal is pressed to the floor but the vehicle does not stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck throttle can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, and damage to property.
symptoms: The throttle sticks
the vehicle idles at high RPM
the vehicle accelerates suddenly
the vehicle hesitates and then lunges forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hesitation when accelerating from idle speed or taking off can cause accidents, especially when merging onto a busy road or when driving uphill.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates when accelerating from idle speed
the vehicle nearly stalls when taking off.
